        const response = await axios.post('http://127.0.0.1:8000/token', {
          username: this.username,
          password: this.password,
        });

        const authStore = useAuthStore();
        authStore.setToken(response.data.access_token);

        this.$router.push('/dashboard');
      } catch (error) {
        alert('Invalid username or password');
      }
    },
  },
};
</script>
```

Now your Vue 3 app is using Pinia as its state management solution. You can continue to expand the authentication store and add more actions, getters, or state properties as needed. Make sure to import and use the `useAuthStore` function in other components to access the authentication state and perform related actions like checking if the user is authenticated, logging out, or fetching user information.

