2. Next, create a new JMS destination (queue) in WebLogic that maps to the RabbitMQ queue you want to consume from. To do this, go to the WebLogic console, navigate to the JMS module you created in step 1, and create a new JMS destination of type "javax.jms.Queue" with a physical name that matches the RabbitMQ queue name. For example:

